I recently met with @uofcincy @Prez_Pinto. It is always great to hear about the work UC is doing for our community. Thanks for the update on the 1819 Innovation Hub and UC’s record enrollment. 

Read more about the 1819 Innovation Hub here:  https://uc1819.com/  pic.twitter.com/q2fh02fyLm
This week, I met with a delegation of Afghan women about the peace process in Afghanistan and how Congress can help protect hard-won freedoms for women in Afghanistan. pic.twitter.com/zlRCxSAXE1

Congratulations to Coach Pat McLaughlin, the head football coach of my alma mater, the La Salle Lancers! https://operations.nfl.com/updates/the-game/2019-don-shula-nfl-high-school-coach-of-the-year-award-nominees-announced/ …

This morning, I read “House Mouse” to around 200 K-3 students at @DelshireElm and presented a flag that had flown over the Capitol to Principal Tara Willig and the students. It was nice meeting you all and keep learning as much as you can! pic.twitter.com/S5LMEt973d

ICYMI: I spoke against H.Con.Res. 83, which seeks to curtail the President’s authority to protect American interests from Iran. 

Watch my full speech here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=1&v=YNb2ClcwvqU&feature=emb_logo …

The House passed @HSBCgop’s H.R. 5078, the Prison to Proprietorship Act. This bill provides a pathway for those incarcerated in federal prisons to be successful, contributing members of society. Thank you Chairwoman @NydiaVelazquez for your leadership in passing this legislation.

This week @HSBCgop’s Subcommittee on Innovation and Workforce Development heard from a panel of experts about the impact of agriculture technology on the nation’s agriculture and food systems. You can read more about the hearing here: https://republicans-smallbusiness.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=403323 …

Great meeting with Irakli Beraia, who just became Chair of the Georgian Parliament’s Foreign Relations Committee. I look forward to continuing to work on strengthening US-Georgian relations. pic.twitter.com/nnB2QkYfZN
